== 分析 ==

=== 结局解读 ===
媒体在文章中详细解读本片结局，帮助观众理解瓦伦丁和温索普是如何在赚取大笔利润同时迫使杜克兄弟破产<ref name="BIWhatHappens">{{cite web | first = Rob | last = Wile | url = https://www.businessinsider.com/trading-places-frozen-concentrated-orange-juice-trade-explained-2013-7?r=US&IR=T | title = Here's What Happened In The Complex Commodity Trade At The End Of 'Trading Places' | date = 2013-07-01 | website = [[商业内幕|Business Insider]] | accessdate = 2020-11-13 | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20200809140829/https://www.businessinsider.com/trading-places-frozen-concentrated-orange-juice-trade-explained-2013-7?r=US&IR=T | archivedate = 2020-08-09 | deadurl = no}}</ref><ref name="NPRWhatHappens">{{cite news | last = Smith | first = Robert | url = https://www.npr.org/sections/money/2013/07/19/201430727/what-actually-happens-at-the-end-of-trading-places | title = What Actually Happens At The End Of 'Trading Places'? | date = 2013-07-12 | publisher = [[全国公共广播电台|NPR]] | accessdate = 2020-11-13 | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20201109034942/https://www.npr.org/sections/money/2013/07/19/201430727/what-actually-happens-at-the-end-of-trading-places | archivedate = 2020-11-09 | deadurl = no}}</ref>。瓦伦丁和温索普炮制的农作物报告令杜克兄弟误以为橙子收成欠佳，供需关系将导致橙子价格上涨，股票、期货都不例外<ref name="TheAtlanticXmas" /><ref name="BIWhatHappens" /><ref name="NPRWhatHappens" />。杜克兄弟企图尽量买入冷冻浓缩橙汁期货操纵市场，因为供应有限时，拥有大量期货自然就能控制冷冻浓缩橙汁的价格，其他交易商明白杜克兄弟的企图后争先恐后加入抢购行列<ref name="BIWhatHappens" /><ref name="NPRWhatHappens" />。每笔期货都代表一定数量的冷冻浓缩橙汁，大量买入导致价格迅速上涨至每磅（约453.59克）1.42美元。温索普和瓦伦丁认为价格已达最高位，于是以该价位卖出，按合同要求他们需在四月按供应冷冻浓缩橙汁。<ref name="TheAtlanticXmas" /><ref name="NPRWhatHappens" />其他经纪人以为农作物报告公布后冷冻浓缩橙汁的价格肯定不止1.42美元，所以竭尽全力从两人手中购买<ref name="TheAtlanticXmas" /><ref name="BIWhatHappens" /><ref name="NPRWhatHappens" />。

接下来公布的真实报告表明橙子作物收成正常，冷冻浓缩橙汁不会短缺，交易商于是又拼命卖出，想尽量减少经济损失，期货价格因此暴跌<ref name="BIWhatHappens" /><ref name="NPRWhatHappens" />。温索普和瓦伦丁于是在每磅29美分低位买入期货，但就是不从杜克兄弟手中买<ref name="BIWhatHappens" /><ref name="NPRWhatHappens" />，这样他们不但赚到每磅高达1.2美元差价，而且这些买入和先前的卖出相抵，四月就不再需要履行任何交货合约<ref name="NPRWhatHappens" />。与此同时，杜克兄弟买下约150万磅冷冻浓缩橙汁期货，最后却一点儿都没卖出去。交易大厅下班时，他们必须交足保证金才能持有期货合约。两人买入的最高价达每磅1.42美元，现在单价都是29美分，要继续持有期货合约就必须交出3.94亿美元资金。杜克兄弟拿不出这么多钱，所以资产全部没收。<ref name="HuffPoWhatHappened">{{cite news | first = Richard James | last = Berry | title = Why The Dukes Went Bust At The End Of Trading Places And Why It's Relevant Today | url = https://www.huffingtonpost.co.uk/richard-james-berry/why-the-dukes-went-bust-a_b_13949584.html | newspaper = [[赫芬顿邮报|The Huffington Post]] | date = 2018-05-01 | accessdate = 2020-11-13 | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20170105184855/https://www.huffingtonpost.co.uk/richard-james-berry/why-the-dukes-went-bust-a_b_13949584.html | archivedate = 2017-01-05 | deadurl = no}}</ref>

=== 主题分析 ===
[[File:The_Prince_and_The_Pauper_-_32-377.jpg|left]]1882年小说《[[乞丐王子|乞丐王子]]》插图。评论认为《颠倒乾坤》是吐温小说《乞丐王子》和《百万英镑》的现代版]]

《颠倒乾坤》的核心剧情是社会阶层截然相反的两人互换身份，评论认为这与[[马克·吐温|马克·吐温]]1881年的小说《[[乞丐王子|乞丐王子]]》异曲同工<ref name="ReviewEBERT" /><ref name="Budd-2002">{{cite book | last = Budd | first = David | title = Culture Meets Culture in the Movies: an Analysis East, West, North, and South, With Filmographies | year = 2002 | publisher = [[麥克法蘭公司出版社|McFarland & Company]] | isbn = 978-0-7864-1095-8 | page = 210 | chapter = Classic Encounters of Black on White | chapter-url = https://archive.org/details/culturemeetscult00budd/page/210  | accessdate = 2020-11-13 }}</ref><ref name="Childs-2006">{{cite book | last = Childs | first = Peter | title = Texts: Contemporary Cultural Texts and Critical Approaches | year = 2006 | publisher = Edinburgh University Press | isbn = 978-0-7486-2043-2 | chapter = Pop Video | page = 44 | accessdate = 2020-11-13 | url = https://books.google.com.tw/books?id=9tmqBgAAQBAJ&q=%22trading+places%22&redir_esc=y#v=snippet&q=%22trading%20places%22}}</ref>。小说讲述相貌异常相似的王子和乞丐临时交换身份，王子尝试贫穷困苦的生活，乞丐享受皇室生活的奢华<ref name="Penguin">{{cite web | url = https://www.penguinrandomhouse.com/books/326591/the-prince-and-the-pauper-by-mark-twain/ | title = The Prince and the Pauper | website = [[企鵝蘭登書屋|Penguin Random House]] | accessdate = 2020-11-13 | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20200718123326/https://www.penguinrandomhouse.com/books/326591/the-prince-and-the-pauper-by-mark-twain/ | archivedate = 2020-07-18 | deadurl = no}}</ref>。《乞丐王子》是白人文学经典之作，但《颠倒乾坤》却让黑人乞丐提升地位，代表对黑人侵占和取代的恐惧<ref name="Childs-2006" />。还有评论将本片与吐温1893年的短篇小说《[[百万英镑|百万英镑]]》（''{{lang|en|The Million Pound Bank Note}}''）对比，该文讲述两兄弟为打赌把无法兑现的一百万英镑支票送给穷人，观察其举止和生活会有什么变化。<ref name="TheAtlanticXmas" /><ref name="IndieWireTidbits" />莫扎特的喜歌剧《费加罗的婚礼》讲述仆人费加罗出于报复挫败富裕雇主的阴谋，评论认为片中采用其中音乐别有深意。片头温索普开车上班时哼起歌剧中的咏叹调《[[你想要跳舞，我的小伯爵|你想要跳舞，我的小伯爵]]》（{{lang|it|Se vuol ballare}}），是费加罗宣称要推翻现行体制的唱段，预示温索普终将击垮杜克兄弟。<ref name="IndieWireTidbits" /><ref name="MONAHAN">{{cite news | first = Mark | last = Monahan | url = https://www.telegraph.co.uk/culture/film/3642337/Must-have-movies-Trading-Places-1983.html | title = Dan Aykroyd Biography | newspaper = [[每日电讯报|The Daily Telegraph]] | date = 2005-05-20 | accessdate = 2020-11-13 | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20190624224546/https://www.telegraph.co.uk/culture/film/3642337/Must-have-movies-Trading-Places-1983.html | archivedate = 2019-06-24 | deadurl = no}}</ref>

《颠倒乾坤》的核心主题是极其富裕和极其贫穷的影响。片中描绘两种极端情境下的生活，一方穷奢极侈，另一方身陷[[贫困文化|贫困文化]]，思维定势和习惯导致他们难以摆脱贫困<ref name="TheAtlanticXmas" />。哈里斯称，电影讽刺贪婪和社会习俗，但结局却是“好人”变得极其富有<ref name="BIOralHistory" />。经济不平等通过富人的生活体现，他们完全与贫困阶层脱节。杜克兄弟的赌局表明两人深感超人一等，根本不在乎包括温索普在内一切社会地位不如他们的人士死活，摧毁他人生活所换“奖赏”不过是高人一等的自豪感。<ref name="TheAtlanticXmas" />作家卡罗琳·安德森（{{lang|en|Carolyn Anderson}}）指出，片中人物（如瓦伦丁）社会地位提升时大多会附上“介绍”桥段，帮他们理解新世界的运作规则。相比之下，[[社會流動|社会地位下降]]的人就没有这种待遇。<ref>{{cite book | first = Carolyn | last = Anderson | editor-last1 = Loukides | editor-first1 = Paul | editor-last2 = Fuller | title = Beyond the Stars: Themes and ideologies in American popular film | chapter = Diminishing Degree of Separation | year = 1990 | publisher = [[鮑林格林州立大學|Bowling Green University Popular Press]] | page = 161 | isbn = 978-0-87972-701-7 | chapter-url = https://books.google.com.tw/books?id=VcpyRHwp-5cC&pg=PA141&dq=%22trading+places%22++movie&redir_esc=y#v=onepage&q=%22trading%20places%22%20&f=false | accessdate = 2020-11-13}}</ref>

文森特·坎比认为，影片在向20世纪早期社会讽刺脱线喜剧致敬时也体现出时代的变迁。早期脱线喜剧推崇除金钱以外其他事物的价值，但《颠倒乾坤》的基础就是金钱价值，以及渴望拥有金钱的人。“英雄”的胜利就是赚大钱，“恶棍”的惩罚就是一贫如洗。英雄所得奖励就是远走高飞到热带岛屿，与过去的贫穷生活彻底剥离。<ref name="ReviewCanby" /><ref name="WAPOSupplySide">{{cite news | first = Stephen | last = Schiff | url = https://www.washingtonpost.com/archive/lifestyle/style/1984/08/26/lights-camera-election/e1535b69-5ce0-46ca-a89c-6227b9776ec1/ | title = Lights! Camera! Election! | date = 1984-08-26 | newspaper = The Washington Post | accessdate = 2020-11-13 | archiveurl = http://archive.is/glHpL | archivedate = 2020-07-06 | deadurl = no}}</ref><ref name="EmpireEssay">{{cite journal | first = Pad | archivedate = 2020-08-09 | deadurl = no | last = Reid | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20200809162929/https://www.empireonline.com/movies/reviews/empire-essay-trading-places-review/ | url = https://www.empireonline.com/movies/reviews/empire-essay-trading-places-review/ | title = Empire Essay: Trading Places Review | date = 2000-01-01 | journal = Empire | accessdate = 2020-11-13}}</ref>片中钱无所不能，变得没钱后，人们迅速诉诸犯罪本能<ref name="TheAtlanticXmas" />，与《[[二八佳人花公子|亚瑟]]》和《[[保送入學|乖仔也疯狂]]》一样堪称[[供給面學派|供給面经济学]]典范。瓦伦丁这种街头骗子拥有平等机遇后工作也能像温索普一样出色，这看似支持左翼政治理念，但片中同时又强调积累财富的重要，鼓吹[[羅納德·雷根的政治立場|里根时代政策]]等右翼思想。<ref name="WAPOSupplySide" />

大卫·巴德（{{lang|en|David Budd}}）认为，《颠倒乾坤》对种族思维定势反其道而行之。伦道夫企图证明后天比先天重要，瓦伦丁拥有同等机遇时能力与温索普相比毫不逊色，在贫困和犯罪中摸爬滚打的过去毫无影响。<ref name="Budd-2002" />两人的赌局结束后，莫蒂默还是打算把瓦伦丁赶回街头：“你真以为我会让[[黑鬼|黑鬼]]经营家族企业？”伦道夫秉持同等立场：“我也不会。”<ref name="EmpireEssay" />巴德认为，影片借此大声疾呼，质疑所谓的公平竞争环境中是否依然包含种族偏见<ref name="Budd-2002" />。赫南·维拉（{{lang|en|Hernan Vera}}）和安德鲁·戈登（{{lang|en|Andrew Gordon}}）指出，片中涉及种族偏见的情节都得到黑人主角同意。片尾两人报复杜克时，温索普[[黑臉扮裝|画上黑脸]]伪装，此举就事先征得瓦伦丁同意，后者还想方设法让古板的温索普放松。如今人们已经普遍认为黑脸扮装是无礼的种族主义举动，但凭借瓦伦丁的许可，如此行为就变得可以接受。温索普在片头导致瓦伦丁蒙冤被捕，后来又想栽赃陷害瓦伦丁入狱以夺回原有职位，但瓦伦丁还是接受并支持温索普。从另一角度来说，杜克兄弟的种族歧视倾向更加明显，瓦伦丁于是同温索普合作，帮他报复昔日雇主。瓦伦丁在本片中更接近传统的“白人”形象，似乎他本来就能在杜克兄弟的世界中生存和适应。<ref>{{cite book | last1 = Vera | first1 = Hernan | last2 = Gordon | first2 = Andrew | title = Screen Saviors: Hollywood Fictions of Whiteness | year = 2003 | publisher = Rowman & Littlefield | isbn = 978-0-8476-9946-9 | chapter = 8: White Out: Racial Masquerade by Whites in American Film I | pages = 126–127 | chapter-url = https://books.google.com.tw/books?id=6ZAPD2YdBXYC&pg=PA127&lpg=PA127&dq=%22trading+places%22+1983&redir_esc=y#v=snippet&q=%22trading%20places%22%20&f=false | accessdate = 2020-11-13}}</ref>

[[史蒂芬·希夫|史蒂芬·希夫]]（{{lang|en|Stephen Schiff}}）声称，电影把金钱描绘成最具价值的东西，这反过来就意味着奥菲莉亚身为妓女，在片中的价值完全源自她善于理财<ref name="WAPOSupplySide" />。哈德利·弗里曼（{{lang|en|Hadley Freeman}}）称，奥菲莉亚就像《蓝精灵》中的蓝妹妹，其他人物都是男子，身为仅有的女子，她的作为就是貌美如花，坐等男人拯救<ref name="GuardianApril2014">{{cite news | first = Hadley | last = Freeman | url = https://www.theguardian.com/film/filmblog/2014/apr/08/my-guilty-pleasure-trading-places | title = My guilty pleasure: Trading Places | date = 2014-04-08 | newspaper = The Guardian | accessdate = 2020-11-13 | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20201024020203/https://www.theguardian.com/film/filmblog/2014/apr/08/my-guilty-pleasure-trading-places | archivedate = 2020-10-24 | deadurl = no}}</ref>。不过，本片一定程度上反其道而行，是奥菲莉亚拯救温索普，帮他在落入谷底万念俱灰之际鼓起生存下去的勇气<ref name="EmpireEssay" />。尼尔·卡伦（{{lang|en|Neal Karlen}}）认为，奥菲莉亚对温索普所说台词“我在这个广阔世界中所能依靠的只有身体、脸蛋和头脑”令人物瞬间丰满，标志着她成为真正有血有肉的人<ref name="RollingStoneOphelia">{{cite journal | first = Neal | last = Karlen | url = https://www.rollingstone.com/movies/movie-features/jamie-lee-curtis-gets-serious-64405/ | title = Jamie Lee Curtis Gets Serious | date = 1985-07-18 | journal = Rolling Stone | accessdate = 2020-11-13 | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20200809113003/https://www.rollingstone.com/movies/movie-features/jamie-lee-curtis-gets-serious-64405/ | archivedate = 2020-08-09 | deadurl = no}}</ref>。

《颠倒乾坤》采用圣诞电影常见套路强调主要人物的孤独感，其中又以温索普为甚。他在圣诞夜企图截赃瓦伦丁，恢复两人之前的社会地位，但这种犯罪行为被当场发现，他也在昔日雇主面前斯文扫地。在商店外等候时，连狗都朝他身上小便。<ref name="Metcalf-1991">{{cite book | last = Metcalf | first = Greg | editor-last1 = Loukides | accessdate = 2020-11-13 | editor-first1 = Paul | editor-last2 = Fuller | editor-first2 = Linda K. | title = Beyond the Stars: Plot conventions in American popular film | chapter = Christmas Conventions of American Films in the 1980s | publisher = Bowling Green University Popular Press | isbn = 978-0-87972-517-4 | pages = 101–102 | chapter-url = https://books.google.com.tw/books?id=w2nqE9V6pToC&pg=PA100&lpg=PA100&dq=%E2%80%9CIt%27s+(Christmas)+Morning+in+America%E2%80%9D:+Christmas+conventions+of+American+films+in+the+1980s%27&redir_esc=y#v=onepage&q=%22trading%20places%22&f=false | year = 1991}}</ref><ref name="DOGXmas">{{cite web | first = Seb | last = Patrick | url = https://www.denofgeek.com/movies/my-favourite-christmas-film-trading-places/ | title = My favourite Christmas film: Trading Places | date = 2008-12-19 | website = Den of Geek | accessdate = 2020-11-13 | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20200809104707/https://www.denofgeek.com/movies/my-favourite-christmas-film-trading-places/ | archivedate = 2020-08-09 | deadurl = no}}</ref>自杀因枪卡壳失败后，天上又开始下雨。次日他融入科尔曼、奥菲莉亚和瓦伦丁组成的“家庭”后境遇才开始转变。<ref name="TheAtlanticXmas" /><ref name="Metcalf-1991" />

== 影响 ==
除影响几位演员的星路外<ref name="BIOralHistory" />，许多评论认为《颠倒乾坤》是史上难得的喜剧佳作，堪称美国喜剧经典<ref name="BIOralHistory" /><ref name="LastingRTList">{{cite web | title = 150 Essential Comedy Movies To Watch Now | url = https://editorial.rottentomatoes.com/guide/essential-comedy-movies/ | website = Rotten Tomatoes  | accessdate = 2020-11-13 | archivedate = 2020-11-06 | deadurl = no | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20201106164613/https://editorial.rottentomatoes.com/guide/essential-comedy-movies/}}</ref><ref name="LastingEmpire">{{cite journal | title = The 50 Greatest Comedies | accessdate = 2020-11-13 | url = https://www.empireonline.com/movies/features/best-comedies/ | journal = Empire | date = 2019-07-31 | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20200821031652/https://www.empireonline.com/movies/features/best-comedies/ | archivedate = 2020-08-21 | deadurl = no}}</ref><ref name="BBC253">{{cite news | url = https://www.bbc.com/culture/article/20170821-the-100-greatest-comedies-of-all-time | title = The 100 Greatest Comedies of all Time | date = 2017-08-22 | publisher = [[英国广播公司|BBC]] | accessdate = 2020-11-13 | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20201028094859/https://www.bbc.com/culture/article/20170821-the-100-greatest-comedies-of-all-time | archivedate = 2020-10-28 | deadurl = no}}</ref><ref name="WGAFunniest2">{{cite web | title = Writers Choose 101 Funniest Screenplays | url = https://www.wga.org/news-events/news/press/2015/writers-choose-101-funniest-screenplays | publisher = Writers Guild of America West | date = 2015-11-11 | accessdate = 2020-11-13 | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20201102004828/https://www.wga.org/news-events/news/press/2015/writers-choose-101-funniest-screenplays | archivedate = 2020-11-02 | deadurl = no}}</ref>。艾克洛德1988年接受采访时称，《颠倒乾坤》、《魔鬼剋星》、《法网》、《福祿雙霸天》和《光棍出差》是他最好的作品<ref name="ChicagoTribuneAList">{{cite news | first = Celia | last = Rivenbark Rich | url = https://www.chicagotribune.com/news/ct-xpm-1988-09-16-8801300799-story.html | title = Dan Aykroyd Shooting for 'A' List Movie | date = 1988-09-16 | newspaper = Chicago Tribune | accessdate = 2002-11-13 | archiveurl = http://archive.is/fJ398 | archivedate = 2020-07-07 | deadurl = no}}</ref>。贝拉米和阿米契在墨菲主演的1988年电影《美国之旅》中再度诠释杜克兄弟，墨菲扮演富裕王子阿基姆（{{lang|en|Akeem}}），把大笔现金送给流离失所的杜克兄弟，莫蒂默告诉伦道夫，这么多钱足够他们重新开始<ref name="IndieWireTidbits" />。墨菲本人表示，《颠倒乾坤》和《美国之旅》他都很喜欢，但如果一定要二选一，他会选择一人分饰多角的《美国之旅》<ref name="YahooMurphy">{{cite web | first = Kevin | last = Polowy | title = Eddie Murphy Chooses 'Coming to America' Over 'Trading Places' | url = https://www.yahoo.com/entertainment/eddie-murphy-chooses-coming-to-america-over-trading-places-171200400.html | website = [[雅虎|Yahoo!]] | date = 2016-09-14 | accessdate = 2020-11-13 | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20200809213339/https://www.yahoo.com/entertainment/eddie-murphy-chooses-coming-to-america-over-trading-places-171200400.html | archivedate = 2020-08-09 | deadurl = no}}</ref>。

据哈里斯透露，曾有人自称因《颠倒乾坤》走上从事金融事业的道路，哈里斯觉得这和电影的理念背道而驰<ref name="BIOralHistory" />。2019年，某匿名人士将拥有的本片版税分成权以14万美元转让，此时这份分成每年可获一万美元<ref name="RoyaltyAuction">{{cite web | title = Film Royalties: Classic Comedy "Trading Places" | url = https://auctions.royaltyexchange.com/auctions/film-royalties-classic-comedy-trading-places/ | website = Royalty Exchange | date = 2019 | accessdate = 2020-11-13 | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20200811000634/https://auctions.royaltyexchange.com/auctions/film-royalties-classic-comedy-trading-places/ | archivedate = 2020-08-11 | deadurl = no}}</ref><ref name="MoneyWatch">{{cite web | first = Brett | last = Arends | title = Looking good, Billy Ray! Rights to 'Trading Places' go up for sale | url = https://www.marketwatch.com/story/looking-good-billy-ray-rights-to-trading-places-go-up-for-sale-2019-02-11 | website = [[市场观察|MarketWatch]] | date = 2019-02-12 | accessdate = 2020-11-13 | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20200712211742/https://www.marketwatch.com/story/looking-good-billy-ray-rights-to-trading-places-go-up-for-sale-2019-02-11 | archivedate = 2020-07-12 | deadurl = no}}</ref>。

2010年，[[商品期货交易委员会|商品期货交易委员会]]主席[[加里·根斯勒|加里·根斯勒]]（{{lang|en|Gary Gensler}}）援引近三十年前上映的《颠倒乾坤》为证，为金融市场提出新规。根斯勒称：
<blockquote>我们建议禁止盗用政府信息参与商品市场交易。艾迪·墨菲主演电影《颠倒乾坤》中的杜克兄弟便是如此，凭借非法获取且尚未公布的[[美国农业部|农业部]]橙类作物报告，他们企图通过购买冷冻浓缩橙汁大发横财。艾迪·墨菲和丹·艾克洛德扮演的角色截获报告后利用信息交易获利并打垮杜克兄弟。<ref name="WSJMurphyRule">{{cite news | first = Matt | last = Phillips | title = First the Volcker Rule, Now the Eddie Murphy Rule! | url = https://www.wsj.com/articles/BL-MB-18853 | newspaper = [[华尔街日报|The Wall Street Journal]] | date = 2010-03-04 | accessdate = 2020-11-13 | archivedate = 2020-11-08 | deadurl = no | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20201108171746/https://www.wsj.com/articles/BL-MB-18853}}</ref></blockquote>上述证词纳入《[[多德-弗兰克法案|多德-弗兰克华尔街改革和消费者保护法案]]》，该法将商品市场的[[內線交易|內線交易]]行为定为非法，其中的第746条又称“艾迪·墨菲法则”<ref name="TheAtlanticXmas" />。

=== 时间的考验 ===
影评人把《颠倒乾坤》评为20世纪80年代难得的喜剧杰作，也是史上有数的圣诞电影佳作<ref name="Bestof80sUSAToday">{{cite journal | first = Charles | last = Stockdale | title = The 75 best movie comedies of the '80s | url = https://www.usatoday.com/story/life/movies/2018/04/20/75-best-movie-comedies-80-s/534907002/ | journal = USA Today | date = 2019-12-15 | accessdate = 2020-11-13 | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20201109041212/https://eu.usatoday.com/story/life/movies/2018/04/20/75-best-movie-comedies-80-s/534907002/ | archivedate = 2020-11-09 | deadurl = no}}</ref><ref name="Bestof80sRT">{{cite web | title = 140 Essential '80s Movies | url = https://editorial.rottentomatoes.com/guide/140-essential-80s-movies/3/ | website = Rotten Tomatoes | accessdate = 2020-11-13 | archivedate = 2020-08-12 | deadurl = no | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20200812140634/https://editorial.rottentomatoes.com/guide/140-essential-80s-movies/3/}}</ref><ref name="LastingRTXmas">{{cite web | title = The 58 Best Christmas Movies Of All Time | url = https://editorial.rottentomatoes.com/guide/best-christmas-movies/ | website = [[爛番茄|Rotten Tomatoes]]  | accessdate = 2020-11-13}}</ref>。2015年，[[美国编剧工会|美国编剧工会]]评选史上101部最风趣的电影剧本，本片和《[[咪走堂|春天不是读书天]]》并列排在第33位<ref name="WGAFunniest2" /><ref name="WGAFunniest1">{{cite web | title = 101 Funniest Screenplays List | url = https://www.wga.org/writers-room/101-best-lists/101-funniest-screenplays/list | publisher = Writers Guild of America West | date = 2015-11-11 | accessdate = 2020-11-13 | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20201105120157/https://www.wga.org/writers-room/101-best-lists/101-funniest-screenplays/list | archivedate = 2020-11-05 | deadurl = no}}</ref>。2017年，[[英国广播公司|英国广播公司]]向来自52个国家和地区的253位评论家（118男135女）征求意见，评选史上最风趣的一百部电影，《颠倒乾坤》排名第74<ref name="BBC253" />。电影还在众多媒体评选的20世纪80年代最佳电影中榜上有名，其中[[美国独立电影频道|独立电影频道]]（{{lang|en|IFC}}）排第八<ref name="Bestof80sIFC">{{cite web | first = Mike | last = Schuster | title = The 11 Best Movie Comedies of the '80s | url = https://www.ifc.com/2016/07/best-comedies-of-the-80s | publisher = IFC | accessdate = 2020-08-09 | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20200809141509/https://www.ifc.com/2016/07/best-comedies-of-the-80s | archivedate = 2020-08-09 | deadurl = yes}}</ref>，[[音樂電視網|音樂電視網]]排17位<ref name="LastingMTV">{{cite news | first = Max | last = Evry | title = The 25 Most Essential '80s Comedies | url = http://www.mtv.com/news/2802897/best-80s-comedies/ | website = [[音樂電視網|MTV.com]] | date = 2011-03-02 | accessdate = 2020-11-13 | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20200714212012/http://www.mtv.com/news/2802897/best-80s-comedies/ | archivedate = 2020-07-14 | deadurl = no}}</ref>，《[[今日美國|今日美國]]》第37<ref name="Bestof80sUSAToday" />，[[爛番茄|爛番茄]]41位<ref name="Bestof80sRT" />，《[[观察家报|观察家报]]》第47<ref>{{cite news | title = The 50 funniest films… chosen by comedians | newspaper = [[观察家报|The Observer]] | date = 2016-12-18 | author = Sarah Millican | deadurl = no | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20201108125247/https://www.theguardian.com/film/2016/dec/18/the-50-funniest-comedy-films-chosen-comedians-stewart-lee-sarah-millican-david-baddiel | accessdate = 2020-11-13 | url = https://www.theguardian.com/film/2016/dec/18/the-50-funniest-comedy-films-chosen-comedians-stewart-lee-sarah-millican-david-baddiel | archivedate = 2020-11-08}}</ref>。部分媒体还把本片列入史上最佳喜剧片之列，如《[[Time_Out|Time Out]]》排名第16<ref name="LastingTimeOut">{{cite journal | first1 = Dave | last1 = Calhoun | first2 = Cath | last2 = Clarke | first3 = Phil | last3 = de Semlyen | first4 = Alim | last4 = Kheraj | first5 = Tom | last5 = Huddleston | first6 = Trevor | last6 = Johnston | first7 = David | last7 = Jenkins | first8 = Kate | last8 = Lloyd | first9 = Tom | last9 = Seymour | first10 = Anna | last10 = Smith | first11 = Ben | last11 = Walters | first12 = Adam Lee | last12 = Davies | first13 = Phil | last13 = Harrison | first14 = Derek | last14 = Adams | first15 = Wally | last15 = Hammond | first16 = Edward | last16 = Lawrenson | fir